name: I-Kebana #2 Hikari
description: I-Kebana is inspired by the Japanese art of arranging flowers with roots in Zen Buddhism and a reverence for nature, the tradition has become both a philosophy and an art. The artwork features stylized 3D plants that take Ikebana into a contemporary context, experimenting with new forms and processes with an emphasis on metacosmic structures. Additional Details: 1080 x 1080 px 60 qps, MP4 16 MB, original audio.
